  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators sought to examine the effects of 'old' red blood cells on mortality and
      morbidity of patients who undergoing revision hip replacement arthroplasty. The investigators
      hypothesis is that patients have an increased risk of mortality and infection after 'old' red
      blood cells transfusions compared with those who received 'new' transfusions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
